summary:
I graduated from Architecture and Urbanism in 2017 at the Faculty of Architecture, University of Zagreb, Croatia, among the top 10 % of students of my generation and was holding the position of an assistant student in several courses at the Department of Designing. Already during my Bachelor studies I started focusing on international architectural practice and had the opportunity to engage in the work of the renowned Cruz y Ortiz Arquitectos office in Seville, Spain. That experience shaped the idea of my professional development to a great deal.  

In 2017, I started working at one of the most perspective young architectural offices in Croatia named ARHIV. There I was a project leader of a complete design of several projects. In the same period I was also independently leading several smaller projects. However, as I was seeking for international professional challenges, I decided to move to Luxembourg where I spent 2 years working in an ambitious architectural office Beiler François Fritsch. There I was focused on housing and urbanistic project of big scale, international competitions, and was in charge of several housing and office projects. 
I moved to Rotterdam to continue my professional growth as a project architect/project lead in BIM environment.
